org.modelio.api.module.contributor

Class AbstractWizardContributor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.api.module.contributor.AbstractWizardContributor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IWizardContributor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDiagramWizardContributor

    public abstract class AbstractWizardContributor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IWizardContributor
    Convenience class that provides an abstract implementation of IDiagramWizardContributor that only provides useful fields and their getters/setters.

    Note to contributor implementors:
    By inheriting from this abstract class you only have to provide implementations for the two abstract methods:

    • checkCanCreateIn(ModelElement)
    • actionPerformed(ModelElement, String, String)
    • IWizardContributor.dispose()

    Since:
    3.4.0

      • findStereotypeFromSpec

        public final Stereotype findStereotypeFromSpec(MClass metaclass,
                                               java.lang.String stereotypeSpec)
        Find the stereotype from a stereotype specification.

        The stereotype specification may have one of the following formats:

        • stereotype name
        • module name#stereotype name
        • module regex#stereotype name
        • module regex#stereotype regex
        Returns null if the specification is null or the stereotype is not found.
        Parameters:
        metaclass - the metaclass to look from
        stereotypeSpec - the stereotype specification
        Returns:
        the found stereotype or null.
